Our Twitter Happy President

Rachel Castellino, Eric Tran, Miles Loef

1/31/2020

Do you ever think about just how much our 45th President of the United States tweets? We all hear about his Twitter activity in the news, but there has got to be a minefield of tweets that may not have been seen by the wider public before his election period. Have you ever wondered if Trumps tweets have gotten more popular over the years? Maybe if he has a certain pattern to his tweets or loves repeating the same words? We felt we must look further into his tweeting history, to unlock some insights about the antics of this man. We used a dataset that has tracked President Trumps tweets from 2009-2020 including the number of retweets, favorites, mentions, and other categories. Lucky for you, our team is here to tackle the behavior of our tweet-happy 45th President of the United States.

Introduction

A quick thank you to GetOldTweets for providing the data for this dataset and to Austin Reese for compiling and condensing this dataset to Kaggle. The original data set includes details about the ID of each tweet, the tweet itself, the date and time stamp of when it was posted, the amount of favorites and retweets it got, and the people he tagged in the tweet itself. There are roughly 42,000 entries - yes you read that right, thats how many tweets Trump has tweeted to date.

This first bar chart here shows the number of tweets he posted every year. Clearly we can see that the frequency of his tweets has increased over the years and peaked during 2013.

This scatterplot shows us his retweets regressed on his favorited tweets; we can see that as his favorites increase, his retweets increase as well, but they dont have a super strong correlation so you cant really say much about this relationship. If youre wondering which was the the tweet on the far left that got the most favorites, it was A\(AP Rocky released from prison and on his way home to the United States from Sweden. It was a Rocky Week, get home ASAP A\)AP!. And the one with the most retweets was # FraudNewsCNN # FNNpic.twitter.com/WYUnHjjUjg.

Analysis

Insight 1: Trump Has Tweeted the Words Fake News Almost 500 Times

Donald Trumps favorite words are exactly the ones you would most associate with him. Our team chose 5 words that we hear Donald Trump use a lot in the news, on social media, and just words we thought fit his personality type the most when tweeting. Of the 5 words fuck, wall, fake news, and tremendous, and loser, we found that Trumps most used words were fake news, wall, and tremendous. Considering how many times he mentions building a tremendous wall on the border of Mexico or calls fake news on almost every relevant news topic, this isnt a surprise.

Insight 2: Trump Tweets the Most Right Before Going to Bed

Sometimes it seems that Trump tweets all day every day. Like. all. the. time. So we decided to see if this was really true- how frequently during different parts of the day does Trump tweet? We found that Trump tweets the most when he is about to go to bed and during the middle of the night- quite a night owl he is. Even when you think hes off golfing, hes tweeting.

Insight 3: Trump Is Most Popular During the Month of August

Now, there has to be some trend of Trumps popularity on Twitter when it gets closer to an election or campaigning time. We combined the number of retweets and favorites his tweets get and plotted it by each month. We can see that as it gets closer and closer to campaigning or election months, his tweets get more popular - the most popular being during August.

Final Thoughts: Trump Tweets A LOT

It turns out there are not too many surprises here. Trump likes to tweet a lot about fake news and his proposed wall. His twitter gets more and more active leading up to election day. Shown by how much he tweets during the middle of the night, we wonder if he sleeps at all. Share your thoughts below, we would love to hear your comments on our Twitter Happy President.
